what that even was.

00:01:12.810 --> 00:01:16.630 align:middle line:10%
Even though, as a boy, you
know, there are intuitions

00:01:16.630 --> 00:01:18.430 align:middle line:10%
and there are openings.

00:01:18.430 --> 00:01:19.810 align:middle line:10%
But from that
particular context,

00:01:19.810 --> 00:01:21.400 align:middle line:10%
you don't know what that is.

00:01:21.400 --> 00:01:23.290 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Well, you created it
from something that wasn't,

00:01:23.290 --> 00:01:23.810 align:middle line:10%
>>BECKWITH: Absolutely.

00:01:23.810 --> 00:01:24.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:01:24.010 --> 00:01:25.610 align:middle line:84%
You created it
from the ground up.

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:26.568 align:middle line:90%
>>BECKWITH: Absolutely.

00:01:26.568 --> 00:01:28.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so, what
gave you that impetus

00:01:28.340 --> 00:01:33.560 align:middle line:84%
to create something that
we all know now as Agape?

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:37.800 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: Well, for me,
I had a spiritual awakening

00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:39.230 align:middle line:90%
back in the '70s.

00:01:39.230 --> 00:01:42.270 align:middle line:84%
I was attending USC as
a psychobiology major.

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:46.260 align:middle line:84%
And I was on my path at the
time to go to medical school.

00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:48.500 align:middle line:84%
And something began
to happen to me.

00:01:48.500 --> 00:01:51.190 align:middle line:84%
I began to have these
interesting dreams

00:01:51.190 --> 00:01:52.430 align:middle line:90%
and interesting openings.

00:01:52.430 --> 00:01:56.490 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, I was
killed in a lucid dream,

00:01:56.490 --> 00:01:59.360 align:middle line:84%
and the pain was
quite excruciating.

00:01:59.360 --> 00:02:01.320 align:middle line:84%
And when I woke up
from that, I could

00:02:01.320 --> 00:02:03.810 align:middle line:84%
see that we were surrounded
by this universal presence

00:02:03.810 --> 00:02:07.310 align:middle line:84%
of such love and such beauty,
that loved me to my core

00:02:07.310 --> 00:02:09.169 align:middle line:90%
and loves everyone to its core.

00:02:09.169 --> 00:02:11.000 align:middle line:84%
And that sent me on
a path to discover

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:12.800 align:middle line:90%
what had happened to me.

00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:14.750 align:middle line:84%
Because I could never
get back in that box.

00:02:14.750 --> 00:02:16.684 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Ah, you remember
that so vividly now?

00:02:16.684 --> 00:02:17.020 align:middle line:90%
Do you remember that?

00:02:17.020 --> 00:02:17.630 align:middle line:90%
>>BECKWITH: Oh absolutely.

00:02:17.630 --> 00:02:18.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:02:18.230 --> 00:02:19.510 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: Oh no,
it's like yesterday.

00:02:19.510 --> 00:02:21.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Gives me chills
when you said that.

00:02:21.540 --> 00:02:24.730 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: In the verb
and the feeling tone

00:02:24.730 --> 00:02:27.930 align:middle line:84%
and the enthusiasm that
happened at that moment,

00:02:27.930 --> 00:02:31.010 align:middle line:84%
for me to discover and
rediscover my real self,

00:02:31.010 --> 00:02:32.930 align:middle line:84%
is still there
when I wake up now.

00:02:32.930 --> 00:02:36.590 align:middle line:84%
And so, one thing led to
another--study, meditation,

00:02:36.590 --> 00:02:39.200 align:middle line:84%
prayer, study,
meditation, prayer,

00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:41.300 align:middle line:84%
ultimately becoming a
spiritual therapist.

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:45.520 align:middle line:84%
And then answering a
call to do a larger work,

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:48.800 align:middle line:84%
going through the resistance
within myself to do that,

00:02:48.800 --> 00:02:50.620 align:middle line:84%
wanting to stay where
I was, and then.

00:02:50.620 --> 00:02:51.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: To be safe.

00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:53.850 align:middle line:90%
>>BECKWITH: Be safe, secure.

00:02:53.850 --> 00:02:56.550 align:middle line:84%
And then at some
point, the energy

00:02:56.550 --> 00:02:58.330 align:middle line:84%
that wants to evolve
through you becomes

00:02:58.330 --> 00:03:00.740 align:middle line:84%
stronger than the
resistance in you.

00:03:00.740 --> 00:03:05.260 align:middle line:84%
And, Agape was born
from that vision.

00:03:05.260 --> 00:03:06.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: From your living room.

00:03:06.960 --> 00:03:09.670 align:middle line:84%
I remember the stories of you
in your living room, talking

00:03:09.670 --> 00:03:12.020 align:middle line:84%
and having these meetings,
just prayer groups,

00:03:12.020 --> 00:03:12.915 align:middle line:90%
just as many have.

00:03:12.915 --> 00:03:15.630 align:middle line:84%
But it kept growing
and growing because it

00:03:15.630 --> 00:03:18.680 align:middle line:84%
was, I mean if you think,
this is your purpose.

00:03:18.680 --> 00:03:20.542 align:middle line:90%
This is you living your destiny.

00:03:20.542 --> 00:03:21.500 align:middle line:90%
>>BECKWITH: Absolutely.

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:25.637 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has a destiny, and
a dimension of my destiny

00:03:25.637 --> 00:03:27.220 align:middle line:84%
was to call a group
of people together

00:03:27.220 --> 00:03:29.560 align:middle line:84%
to start a vision
group, in which we

00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:31.605 align:middle line:90%
asked a very powerful question.

00:03:31.605 --> 00:03:35.110 align:middle line:84%
And the question was, what
would we have to become,

00:03:35.110 --> 00:03:36.870 align:middle line:84%
in order to manifest
this community

00:03:36.870 --> 00:03:38.350 align:middle line:90%
of unconditional love?

00:03:38.350 --> 00:03:42.950 align:middle line:84%
So the question helped us grow
and unfold and actually evolve

00:03:42.950 --> 00:03:46.570 align:middle line:84%
to become the vehicles
through which this idea could

00:03:46.570 --> 00:03:47.440 align:middle line:90%
come through.

00:03:47.440 --> 00:03:49.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And for people
that may not know Agape,

00:03:49.430 --> 00:03:53.290 align:middle line:84%
tell us about the philosophy,
the nondenominational

00:03:53.290 --> 00:03:56.740 align:middle line:84%
philosophy that you
created basically.

00:03:56.740 --> 00:03:58.330 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: Well,
basically we call

00:03:58.330 --> 00:04:01.130 align:middle line:84%
it a transdenominational
spiritual community, which

00:04:01.130 --> 00:04:03.020 align:middle line:84%
means it goes
beyond denomination,

00:04:03.020 --> 00:04:06.310 align:middle line:84%
cuts across beyond
denominations,

00:04:06.310 --> 00:04:11.650 align:middle line:84%
and embraces the spiritual
truths of all the sacred paths.

00:04:11.650 --> 00:04:14.570 align:middle line:84%
And so, we're keenly aware that
this presence that we call God,

00:04:14.570 --> 00:04:18.220 align:middle line:84%
love, intelligence is
everywhere in its fullness.

00:04:18.220 --> 00:04:19.500 align:middle line:90%
And that we are its image.

00:04:19.500 --> 00:04:21.010 align:middle line:90%
We are its likeness.

00:04:21.010 --> 00:04:24.050 align:middle line:84%
And that we have the capacity
to reflect and to reveal it.

00:04:24.050 --> 00:04:26.750 align:middle line:84%
We have the capacity to
reflect and reveal the cosmos

00:04:26.750 --> 00:04:28.790 align:middle line:84%
in a way that has
never happened before.

00:04:28.790 --> 00:04:31.820 align:middle line:84%
And so, through affirmative
prayer, meditation, life

00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:35.720 align:middle line:84%
visioning, we seek
to open ourselves up

00:04:35.720 --> 00:04:37.802 align:middle line:84%
to the infinite
possibilities within us

00:04:37.802 --> 00:04:39.510 align:middle line:84%
to make a mighty
difference on the planet

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:40.969 align:middle line:84%
during our time of
our incarnation.

00:04:40.969 --> 00:04:43.134 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because those things
that you just mentioned

00:04:43.134 --> 00:04:45.660 align:middle line:84%
are universal, truly with
all religions, aren't they?

00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:49.250 align:middle line:84%
Through affirmative
prayer, and visioning.

00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:52.385 align:middle line:84%
That's really what all religion
does in some form or another,

00:04:52.385 --> 00:04:52.890 align:middle line:90%
isn't it?

00:04:52.890 --> 00:04:54.431 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: Well,
ultimately religion

00:04:54.431 --> 00:04:58.130 align:middle line:84%
is supposed to take us
to a spiritual encounter,

00:04:58.130 --> 00:05:00.340 align:middle line:84%
an existential encounter,
with the Absolute,

00:05:00.340 --> 00:05:01.450 align:middle line:90%
with the Presence.

00:05:01.450 --> 00:05:04.970 align:middle line:84%
It's not to keep us in
a dogmatic believing

00:05:04.970 --> 00:05:06.140 align:middle line:90%
of a particular religion.

00:05:06.140 --> 00:05:09.560 align:middle line:84%
It's actually a vehicle
to the transcendent.

00:05:09.560 --> 00:05:13.420 align:middle line:84%
And so, we wanted to develop
a community of individuals

00:05:13.420 --> 00:05:17.270 align:middle line:84%
that would come and participate
in their own unfolding,

00:05:17.270 --> 00:05:20.590 align:middle line:84%
discover their gifts,
give them to the world,

00:05:20.590 --> 00:05:23.070 align:middle line:84%
be a beneficial
presence on the planet.

00:05:23.070 --> 00:05:25.330 align:middle line:84%
And kind of make a
vow that the world

00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:27.110 align:middle line:84%
would be better
before we left it.

00:05:27.110 --> 00:05:27.640 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:05:27.640 --> 00:05:28.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes.

00:05:28.860 --> 00:05:30.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean there's
statistics out there that

00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:32.500 align:middle line:84%
say 90 something
percent of people

00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:35.610 align:middle line:84%
believe in God, a
God of some type.

00:05:35.610 --> 00:05:40.150 align:middle line:84%
But yet people are moving
away from organized religion,

00:05:40.150 --> 00:05:40.934 align:middle line:90%
statistically.

00:05:40.934 --> 00:05:41.600 align:middle line:90%
>>BECKWITH: Yes.

00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:42.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In the US, at least.

00:05:42.950 --> 00:05:45.764 align:middle line:84%
Have you found that
amongst your congregation?

00:05:45.764 --> 00:05:47.180 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that
those people are

00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:50.490 align:middle line:84%
the ones that seem to
find you online, as well?

00:05:50.490 --> 00:05:52.360 align:middle line:84%
Here there's an online
presence, as well.

00:05:52.360 --> 00:05:55.650 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: Yeah, we
have the survivors

00:05:55.650 --> 00:05:59.460 align:middle line:84%
of traditional religion, people
who walked away from religion.

00:05:59.460 --> 00:06:03.280 align:middle line:84%
And we have individuals who
used to call themselves atheist.

00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:07.920 align:middle line:84%
We have individuals who
would check the box, none,

00:06:07.920 --> 00:06:10.340 align:middle line:84%
if, in fact, they say, what
religion do you belong to?

00:06:10.340 --> 00:06:12.250 align:middle line:84%
But they did believe
in a higher power.

00:06:12.250 --> 00:06:15.810 align:middle line:84%
They believe that there
was some cosmic force that

00:06:15.810 --> 00:06:17.720 align:middle line:90%
was behind everything.

00:06:17.720 --> 00:06:20.560 align:middle line:84%
So we have all those
people in one room.

00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:24.150 align:middle line:84%
Plus we have the Buddhists,
the Sikhs, the Christians,

00:06:24.150 --> 00:06:27.410 align:middle line:84%
the Muslims--all there
in the same room,

00:06:27.410 --> 00:06:30.310 align:middle line:84%
celebrating the Divine Presence
that's within all of us.

00:06:30.310 --> 00:06:33.830 align:middle line:84%
And developing a
spiritual practice

00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:36.330 align:middle line:84%
that allows them,
on a daily basis,

00:06:36.330 --> 00:06:39.070 align:middle line:84%
to be a candidate for
what I call an existential

00:06:39.070 --> 00:06:41.072 align:middle line:84%
encounter with the
Divine, with the Presence.

00:06:41.072 --> 00:06:41.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yeah.

00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:45.717 align:middle line:84%
And being in the community
there, it is so spirit-raising,

00:06:45.717 --> 00:06:48.050 align:middle line:84%
and the music ministry and
everything that comes with it

00:06:48.050 --> 00:06:48.750 align:middle line:90%
is great.

00:06:48.750 --> 00:06:51.130 align:middle line:84%
You've had the opportunity to
have audiences with several

00:06:51.130 --> 00:06:53.060 align:middle line:84%
of the leaders of our
country, because they've

00:06:53.060 --> 00:06:55.309 align:middle line:84%
caught on to what you're
doing as being something that

00:06:55.309 --> 00:07:00.830 align:middle line:84%
is, not only progressive, but
has made a mark in this world.

00:07:00.830 --> 00:07:04.635 align:middle line:84%
You had a meeting with Obama,
before he was President

00:07:04.635 --> 00:07:05.760 align:middle line:90%
or was it the end of his so

00:07:05.760 --> 00:07:07.790 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: No, that was when
he was running the first time.

00:07:07.790 --> 00:07:08.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: First time, OK.

00:07:08.460 --> 00:07:10.085 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: There
was a private meeting

00:07:10.085 --> 00:07:11.760 align:middle line:84%
