00:23:09.880 --> 00:23:12.440 align:middle line:90%
Where do we forget that?

00:23:12.440 --> 00:23:15.190 align:middle line:84%
At what point does that
get programmed out?

00:23:15.190 --> 00:23:17.055 align:middle line:84%
Because it definitely
isn't the norm.

00:23:17.055 --> 00:23:17.680 align:middle line:90%
>>BECKWITH: No.

00:23:17.680 --> 00:23:22.440 align:middle line:84%
I think that when, as a child,
most children their imagination

00:23:22.440 --> 00:23:23.800 align:middle line:90%
is unfettered.

00:23:23.800 --> 00:23:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And they have what we
call the beginner's mind.

00:23:27.580 --> 00:23:30.730 align:middle line:90%
And they dream big.

00:23:30.730 --> 00:23:35.540 align:middle line:84%
They have gigantic possibilities
that are in front of them.

00:23:35.540 --> 00:23:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And little by little, we
teach them to be serious

00:23:38.900 --> 00:23:41.810 align:middle line:84%
about the world and
about their survival.

00:23:41.810 --> 00:23:44.180 align:middle line:84%
And we start to
shrink their dream.

00:23:44.180 --> 00:23:48.360 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, what happens
is, not only does their dream

00:23:48.360 --> 00:23:53.240 align:middle line:84%
shrink and fear is injected
about their future,

00:23:53.240 --> 00:23:55.380 align:middle line:84%
but then they, somewhere
along the line,

00:23:55.380 --> 00:23:58.990 align:middle line:84%
we pick up the idea that our
good is outside of ourselves.

00:23:58.990 --> 00:24:03.960 align:middle line:84%
And that the answers are
outside of ourselves,

00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:05.990 align:middle line:84%
even the educational
system, if we

00:24:05.990 --> 00:24:09.710 align:middle line:84%
want to call it that, it's
the form of kind of a banking

00:24:09.710 --> 00:24:13.230 align:middle line:84%
education where we try to
put things into children,

00:24:13.230 --> 00:24:14.780 align:middle line:84%
rather than trying
to pull them out.

00:24:14.780 --> 00:24:16.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And they have to spit
them out on test and so forth.

00:24:16.940 --> 00:24:18.660 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH: So it's
an antiquated system

00:24:18.660 --> 00:24:19.950 align:middle line:90%
that we're living under.

00:24:19.950 --> 00:24:21.820 align:middle line:84%
So you put all that
together, and you end up

00:24:21.820 --> 00:24:25.370 align:middle line:84%
having adults that are living
life looking for the answers

00:24:25.370 --> 00:24:26.850 align:middle line:90%
outside of themselves.

00:24:26.850 --> 00:24:30.060 align:middle line:84%
They have-- their vision is not
bigger than their television

00:24:30.060 --> 00:24:31.120 align:middle line:90%
screen.

00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:34.080 align:middle line:84%
And they're seeking
mainly to survive.

00:24:34.080 --> 00:24:36.620 align:middle line:84%
And then, fortunately,
what the universe

00:24:36.620 --> 00:24:40.880 align:middle line:84%
has for them is an existential
crisis, midlife crises which

00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:43.740 align:middle line:84%
generally is the evolutionary
impulse trying to break them

00:24:43.740 --> 00:24:47.110 align:middle line:84%
through the small vision that
they have about themselves.

00:24:47.110 --> 00:24:50.090 align:middle line:84%
And so if they
don't anesthetize--

00:24:50.090 --> 00:24:51.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Anesthetize
themselves against it.

00:24:51.840 --> 00:24:53.655 align:middle line:84%
>>BECKWITH:
--against the crisis.

00:24:53.655 --> 00:24:56.355 align:middle line:84%
They can wake up,
and say, oh, my God.

00:24:56.355 --> 00:24:57.730 align:middle line:84%
I've been sleeping
my whole life.

00:24:57.730 --> 00:24:58.354 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what
you hear mostly.

